records.addlTxt:
Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Amended Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.   Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:

The Court ordered defendant to serve 9 months at the House of Correction, with release to the Community Justice Resource Center (CJRC) ONLY.  Credit for 52 days time served.  Court would allow good time.

While serving his sentence at the CJRC, the Court ordered the following:
 - No alcohol or controlled substances;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Be given parenting classes/counseling and job and vocational training;
 - Seek and maintain employment.

Court ordered defendant to pay the DNA surcharge, plus costs, disbursements and surcharges, to be paid within one (1) year of today's date (6/03/15).  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant, which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
